Anh - Anh
UFO
[ju:ɛf'əʊ, 'ju:fəʊ]
■ noun (plural UFOs) a mysterious object seen in the sky for which it is claimed no orthodox scientific explanation can be found, popularly said to be vehicles carrying extraterrestrials.
Derivatives
ufologicaladjective
ufologistnoun
ufologynoun
Origin
1950s: acronym from unidentified flying object.

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
UFO
n.
unidentified flying object
1) to sight a UFO
2) (misc.) a UFO sighting

sentences.en: In 1978, what happened after an Australian said he saw a UFO?

sentences.en: In 1978, a young pilot and his plane disappeared after sighting a UFO.
